The former Chief Minister and national vice-president of Bharatiya Janata Party B.S. Yeddyurappa has reiterated that he will continue in the State politics.Addressing presspersons here on Wednesday, Mr. Yeddyurappa said that he would strive to strengthen the BJP in Karnataka and bring the party back to power.To a query, he said that he was not an aspirant for a berth in the Union Cabinet nor for the post of president of the BJPâ€™s State unit. The central leaders of BJP would take an appropriate decision on the appointment of the president of State unit, he said.On the verdict of the High Court quashing 15 first-information reports registered against him , Mr. Yeddyurappa said that it had boosted his morale.